A friend of Peaches Geldof's late mother has claimed she desperately tried to confront the young model over her drug abuse, while friends who knew about her heroin addiction 'turned blind eyes'.

Gerry Agar, the former publicist of Paula Yates, said she reached out to Peaches six years ago in a bid to stop her suffering the same fate as her mother, who died of an accidental heroin overdose when Peaches was 11.

But she said Peaches, a mother-of-two, suffered after those around her 'said nothing' - despite the 25-year-old relapsing.

