In November 2013, a drugs test showed her to be clean and Mr Cohen believed she had defeated the habit.

But Mr Cohen, a 24-year-old musician, told the inquest she relapsed in February and was hiding heroin in the loft.

When he confronted her about it, she 
retrieved a stash she had hidden in the loft and flushed it down the toilet to show
 she was serious about giving up. But she failed to break the habit.

Mr Hatch said Peaches' death was not quite history repeating itself, in regards to Miss Yates' death, because Miss Geldof had tried to 
break her addiction and had returned to the drug for reasons no one 
would ever know.

She had 3mg per litre of diamorphine, the chemical name for heroin, in her blood. Her mother had 0.3mg when she died.

